# Full Parameter and Variable Names

Use full, descriptive names for parameters and variables. Avoid single-letter or overly abbreviated names.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
modifiers.forEach((modifier) => { ... })
items.map((item, index) => ...)
const { store } = useStore()
for (const series of data.series) { ... }

// ❌ BAD
modifiers.forEach((m) => { ... })
items.map((x, i) => ...)
const { s } = useStore()
for (const s of data.series) { ... }
```

**Examples:**
- `modifiers` not `m`
- `index` not `i`
- `store` not `s`
- `series` not `s` (when iterating series)
- `item` or full noun (e.g. `shape`, `series`) not `s` or `x`
